{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17639634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17639634"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:07:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:07:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17783"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17783","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17783"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10497"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72449"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10497","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10497"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17783"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57919"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4932"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10198"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24498"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24559"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72449","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72449"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ENail growth is a continuous process throughout life, with different growth rates observed in different locations of the body.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the average monthly growth rate of fingernails in healthy adults?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["1.5 mm per month","7.0 mm per month","3.5 mm per month","10.0 mm per month","0.5 mm per month"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe average fingernail growth rate is \u003Cstrong\u003E3.5 mm per month\u003C/strong\u003E in healthy adults. This rate is approximately three times faster than toenail growth. Understanding normal nail growth rates is important for assessing various pathological conditions affecting nail growth.\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E0.5 mm per month\u003C/strong\u003E represents a growth rate that is too slow, as even toenails grow more rapidly than this.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E1.5 mm per month\u003C/strong\u003E approximates the normal growth rate of toenails rather than fingernails.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E7.0 mm per month\u003C/strong\u003E describes a growth rate that exceeds normal physiological limits.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E10.0 mm per month\u003C/strong\u003E indicates an impossibly rapid growth rate that is not compatible with normal nail physiology.\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E    \u003Cp\u003ENail growth rates can be affected by various factors including age (slower in elderly), nutrition (poor nutrition decreases growth), circulation (peripheral vascular disease slows growth), and local factors such as trauma or inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fingernails grow approximately 3.5 mm per month, which is three times faster than toenails.","Nail growth is influenced by factors including age, nutrition, circulation, and trauma.","The nail matrix produces the nail plate through continuous cell division and keratinisation."],"references":["Hall JE, Hall ME. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020.","Tortora, G. J., Mellifont, R., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Peoples, G., D, D. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, Asia-Pacific Edition,  2nd Edition. John Wiley \u0026 Sons Australia; 2019."]},"rela